Mabul.title: Mabul
Mabul.byline: Mabul Island (Pulau Mabul in Malay) is a small island off the south-east coast of Sabah in Malaysian Borneo.

Mabinay.title: Mabinay
Mabinay.byline: Mabinay (stress on middle syllable) is a municipality covering a large area of hills and valleys near the center of Negros Island.

Mabini.title: Mabini
Mabini.byline: Mabini is a municipality in Batangas lying on a peninsula overlooking Batangas and Balayan Bays, and considered the birthplace of Philippine's scuba diving industry.
